			<!-- more about him -->
			<div class="he">
				<h2>About Tac</h2>
				<p>
Born in Ft. Bragg N.C. to Robert and Sandy Tacelosky, he lived the life of an army brat, moving frequently, but always answered "New Jersey" to the question: "Where did you grow up?"  After getting a degree in Electrical Engineering from Villanova, he spent 10 years in San Diego, where he started MicroTac Software, which made computerized translation software.  After selling the company, he moved to Washington, DC in 1994 and spent the next phase of his life fighting Big Tobacco, including co-founding Smokefree DC, the grassroots group that was instrumental in getting the current smokefree legislation passed.  He currently spends too much time working on technology projects and hopes to someday to go into filmmaking.
</p><p>
He looks forward to the next phase of his life, being married to Linda, and to whatever future that may hold.
</p>
				</p>
